<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-27T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1614: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-27T11:00:00-05:00">April 27, 1933—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>96. Department’s No. 94, April 12, 6 p.m. The following telegram has been
                            received from Bogotá:</p>
                        <p>(Here quote telegram No. 46, April 21, 5 p.m., from Bogotá.)</p>
                        <p>This formula seems to provide an eminently fair and reasonable settlement
                            of the Leticia affair and you may informally so inform Lester.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>